# Cloudinary Image Patterns

## Upload (Client)
Use `CldUploadButton` from `next-cloudinary` with preset `bumpity-road`:
```tsx
import { CldUploadButton, CldImage } from "next-cloudinary";

<CldUploadButton
  uploadPreset="bumpity-road"
  onSuccess={(result) => {
    const info = result.info as { secure_url: string; public_id: string; width: number; height: number };
    setImage({ url: info.secure_url, publicId: info.public_id });
  }}
  className="rounded-md bg-primary px-4 py-2 text-sm text-primary-foreground"
>
  Upload Image
</CldUploadButton>
```

## Display (Client)
Use `CldImage` for optimized display:
```tsx
<CldImage src={publicId} alt="description" width={400} height={300} crop="fill" className="rounded-lg" />
```
For non-Cloudinary URLs or lightbox, use plain `<img>` with `/* eslint-disable @next/next/no-img-element */`.

## Deletion (Server)
In API DELETE routes, always clean up Cloudinary images before database deletion:
```typescript
import { deleteCloudinaryImage, deleteCloudinaryImages } from "@/utils/cloudinary";

// Single image
await deleteCloudinaryImage(entry.imagePublicId);

// Multiple images (chunks of 100)
await deleteCloudinaryImages(publicIds);
```

## Database Fields
Store both URL and public ID for every image:
```prisma
imageUrl      String
imagePublicId String
```
Some models store arrays: `imageUrls String[]`, `imagePublicIds String[]` (e.g., LoonObservation).
